           <div type="translation" source="bib:Chhom2011_01"><!-- kuch: The term 'slave' should be understood as 'servant'. -->
 	<p n="1-7">Village of At Dhvājaya: Si Īśvaramaya, Gho Kaṁpit, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Kaṁpañ, Gho Candra<gap reason="lost"/>, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Saṁ-ap, Gvāl La-au, Tai Saṁ-ap, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Kañ-yān, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Kañjaṅ, Tai Saṁ-ap, Tai Kaṁpit, Tai Kaṁprvat, Lap Thgau accompanied by two sons <supplied reason="explanation">a boy at the age of running and a baby</supplied>. Total: 8 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, an animal keeper <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied>, 8 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>, a male slave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>lap</foreign></supplied>, a boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied> and a baby boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied>; grand total 20.</p>
              <p n="7-10">Village of <gap reason="lost"/>.</p>
              <p n="11-23"><gap reason="lost"/>, another <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Oṅkāra, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Saṁ-ap, <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Kaṁvrau, Gho Vidyā, <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Kūs, <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Nala, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Kaṁprvat, <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Kan-u, Tai Kaṁpit, another Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, another Tai Kan-hyaṅ, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, another Tai Kaṁpit, <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Mukti, <gap reason="lost"/>. Total: 39 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, <gap reason="lost"/>. Among the <foreign>lvan</foreign> people, there are: Gho Kan-ī, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>,</p>
              <p n="24-30"><gap reason="lost"/></p>
